==Classical Nahuatl==
{{wikipedia|Atlatl}}
[[Image:Atlatl.png|thumb|right]]
===Alternative spellings===
*[[atlatl#Classical_Nahuatl|atlatl]]
===Etymology===
'''[[ah-]]''' "not" + '''[[tlatl]]''' "strip of cloth", i.e. "a non-[[sling#English|sling]]".
===Noun===
'''ahtlatl''' (''possessed'' '''[[iahtlauh|īahtlauh]]''')

#An [[atlatl]]; a [[spear-thrower]].
===References===
*Andrews, J. Richard. (2003) ''Workbook for Introduction to Classical Nahuatl, Revised Edition'' Univeristy of Oklahoma Press, p. 207.
*Karttunen, Frances. (1983) ''An Analytical Dictionary of Nahuatl'' University of Texas Press, p. 7.
